snippet.textDisplay:
The sad reality is that whole generations of children grew up in schools and cultures that saw a kid with ADHD and just considered them lazy. Determined them unworthy of effort cause they "didn't want to learn."

I mean shit twice a week they would pull me out of class to give me instruction on improving my hand writing cause a teacher complained about not being able to read it.

Can't imagine what could have happened if a teacher had spoken up about my lack of attention span in a way that maybe could have gotten me some help. Didn't get an official diagnosis until I was 23 from a therapist. Thanks for this song, shit thanks for the whole album. It means a lot to people like me.
